The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Normality hope in report

 OUR BUREAU

 Calcutta/Midnapore, June 14: The state government today told the high court that normality would be restored in the disturbed areas in and around Nandigram within a week.

 In its report, submitted by home secretary Prasad Ranjan Ray, the government said the orders issued by the court on May 3 regarding steps to restore normality had been carried out.

 The report also said that all political parties had been showing keen interest to restore normality in the disturbed areas and extending co-operation to the peace process. If efforts by the parties to restore peace in Nandigram continue, the entire area will be normal soon, the report said.

 The government said that since 10 last night, several people who had fled their homes had returned. It is a fact that after returning home some people are facing minor problems. But it is believed that the situation will change soon, the report stated.




